{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.76",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 76,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 76 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:1",
      "text": "Unto the end, for Idithun, a psalm of Asaph.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:2",
      "text": "I cried to the Lord with my voice; to God with my voice, and he gave ear to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:3",
      "text": "In the days of my trouble I sought God, with my hands lifted up to him in the night, and I was not deceived. My soul refused to be comforted:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:4",
      "text": "I remembered God, and was delighted, and was exercised, and my spirit swooned away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:5",
      "text": "My eyes prevented the watches: I was troubled, and I spoke not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:6",
      "text": "I thought upon the days of old: and I had in my mind the eternal years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:7",
      "text": "And I meditated in the night with my own heart: and I was exercised and I swept my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:8",
      "text": "Will God then cast off for ever? or will he never be more favourable again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:9",
      "text": "Or will he cut off his mercy for ever, from generation to generation?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:10",
      "text": "Or will God forget to shew mercy? or will he in his anger shut up his mercies?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:11",
      "text": "And I said, Now have I begun: this is the change of the right hand of the most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:12",
      "text": "I remembered the works of the Lord: for I will be mindful of thy wonders from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:13",
      "text": "And I will meditate on all thy works: and will be employed in thy inventions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:14",
      "text": "Thy way, O God, is in the holy place: who is the great God like our God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:15",
      "text": "Thou art the God that dost wonders. Thou hast made thy power known among the nations:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:16",
      "text": "With thy arm thou hast redeemed thy people the children of Jacob and of Joseph.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:17",
      "text": "The waters saw thee, O God, the waters saw thee: and they were afraid, and the depths were troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:18",
      "text": "Great was the noise of the waters: the clouds sent out a sound. For thy arrows pass:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:19",
      "text": "The voice of thy thunder in a wheel. Thy lightnings enlightened the world: the earth shook and trembled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:20",
      "text": "Thy way is in the sea, and thy paths in many waters: and thy footsteps shall not be known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.76.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:21",
      "text": "Thou hast conducted thy people like sheep, by the hand of Moses and Aaron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
